Themba Zwane of Mamelodi Sundowns. JOHANNESBURG - The Premier Soccer League end-of-season awards were dished out Thursday night. Unsurprisingly Mamelodi Sundowns came away with the top hounours. Star midfielder, Themba Zwane walked away with three major awards. He took the prestigious Player of the Year award. READ: Ronaldo still positive for coronavirus: reports He also won the midfielder of the year award and completed his hattrick by being chosen as Players' Player of the year by his peers. Zwane's former coach, Pitso Mosimane, now with Al Ahly in Egypt, has been named coach of the year for a record third year in a row. Mosimane led Sundowns to the treble before his shock move to Cairo.